title: Question for the real estate experts about Gov. Inslee's evictions moratorium and freeze on residential rent increases.
text:
I've got tenants in a couple of properties around the Seattle area.  One of them has a lease ending in May.

What happens if they don't want to move out by the end of May, and I don't want to renew their lease?

Can they stay in my property, free of threat from eviction, even if they're off-lease?
